# UI: Prefer XML Over Lua

Define UI in XML when possible. Do **not** do basic UI setup in Lua if it can be done in XML.

- **In XML**: textures (file path, layer, anchors), sizes, anchors, backdrop when supported, font strings, simple layout.
- **In Lua only when necessary**: dynamic values, behavior (OnClick, OnShow, etc.), things XML cannot express or that Blizzard’s schema doesn’t support.

Avoid creating or setting textures, anchors, or sizes in Lua when the same can be declared in the frame’s XML (e.g. `<Layers><Layer><Texture file="...">` with `<Anchors>`).
